    "en": {
      "title": "Another 10 years to clear the Ukrainian mine",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "It is estimated that it will take at least a decade for Ukraine to clear its land and landmines of land mines and explosives after the end of the conflict with Russia.",
        "Ukraine has cleared 620 square kilometers of land filled with thousands of explosives, including 2,000 aerial bombs, but nearly 300,000 square kilometers are still at risk.",
        "It covers about half the territory of Ukraine and is as large as Italy, said Alexander Koronzhi, a spokesman for Ukraine's state emergency service."
      ],
